values (true, 'Senior UI Developer · Angular & React', 'About Me', $jsonval$["I'm Jaymin Maheta, a Senior UI Developer with 6+ years of experience turning complex product requirements into interfaces that feel effortless to use. I work at the layer where design intent meets shipped code — the layer where good ideas either survive contact with real data, real browsers, and real users, or they don't.", "My path started in the trenches of responsive marketing pages, where I learned that a layout is only as good as its worst viewport. From there I moved into building and owning shared component libraries — first in React, then in Angular with PrimeNG — because I kept noticing the same buttons, the same modals, the same form patterns being rebuilt slightly differently by every team that touched them. Consolidating that drift into a single, well-documented system became the thread that runs through most of my career since.", "That thread has taken me across healthcare, productivity, and fintech products — three domains with very different stakes but the same underlying question: how do you make dense, high-consequence information legible at a glance? In healthcare that meant record lookups fast enough to matter during patient care. In fintech it meant financial tables that stayed precise without becoming visually overwhelming. In productivity tools it meant stripping away chrome until the task itself was the loudest thing on screen.", "Along the way I've led design-system rollouts from Figma file to production component library, partnered directly with designers over Zeplin handoff to keep implementation and intent in sync, and mentored teams of 200+ across delivery cycles — reviewing pull requests, pairing through gnarly CSS bugs, and setting the accessibility bar a little higher each time.", "I care most about the details most users never consciously notice: load-bearing accessibility that survives a screen reader and a keyboard-only pass, motion that respects intent instead of decorating it, and code that's as maintainable six months later as the interface is polished on day one."]$jsonval$::jsonb)
on conflict (id) do update set eyebrow = excluded.eyebrow, heading = excluded.heading, paragraphs = excluded.paragraphs;

